Collagen vascular diseases of childhood.
 This article is devoted to collagen vascular diseases of childhood.
 The connective tissue diseases that are discussed are lupus erythematosus, scleroderma, and dermatomyositis.
 Of the vasculitic syndromes, Henoch-Schonlein purpura, acute hemorrhagic edema of infancy, and polyarteritis nodosa are discussed.
 Although the collagen vascular diseases are rare in the pediatric age group, when they occur they can be very serious.
